= <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> Congress

Walther Lambach has been a divisive figure, alienating nearly every faction within the party—a feat only Hugenberg had previously accomplished. Under normal circumstances, he would have been removed long ago, but his efforts to expand the influence of his <span style="color: #6D5298;">Christian Socialist</span> faction have made the wider party wary of another split, yet another parallel to Hugenberg.

The turmoil within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> appears to be endless. First came Hugenberg’s split, then the Young Plan debacle and the Christian Socialist takeover—now Lambach is pushing to open the party to <span style="color: #000000;">repu</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">bli</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">cans</span> as he first outlined in his controversial article that started this whole mess years ago. Meanwhile, the economic crisis and the rising <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>, threatening to eclipse the party, have only added fuel to the fire.

- @lambach: Lambach solidifies the party’s <span style="color: #6D5298;">Christian Socialist</span> direction.
- @lambach_ousted: Lambach is taken down in a simple vote of no confidence.

