arty’s tarnished reputation among rural voters after Lambach’s tenure.?]The new agrarian focus of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has alienated the working-class voters initially drawn to Lambach. In response, the <span style="color: #6D5298;">Christian Socialist</span> wing attempts to counteract this by successfully pressuring Schiele and Westarp to retain some of its worker-friendly provisions in its program.

